Day 297 • at the crack of dawn

Learning a foreign language changed my life. 

It broadened my horizons and unlocked a completely new culture. 

Along the way, it reshaped how I see the world. It taught me that perspective isn’t fixed. It evolves with every new word, conversation, and cultural insight.

Speaking someone’s native language is more than just communication. It’s connection. 

It lets you form real friendships, often with people living thousands of kilometers away, people you might never have crossed paths with otherwise.

I began learning Japanese exactly five years ago. Who would have imagined that dedicating just 30 to 60 minutes a day could lead to something so deeply rewarding?

What do I always say? Never underestimate the power of compounding. Small, consistent actions- done daily & quietly, can lead to mastery over time.

NOT DONE YET. 

会えてめっちゃ嬉しかった！！☺️ 

またすぐ会おうねっ！また今度！
